HEADWORD: Kaiser
<hw>Kai"ser</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr., fr. L.
<ets>Caesar</ets>. Cf. <er>Kesar</er>, and <er>Czar</er>.]</ety>
<def>The ancient title of emperors of Germany assumed by <person>King
William of Prussia</person> when crowned sovereign of the new German
empire in 1871.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

